[1] Portugal [Porto]
Date: Sat 25 Mar 2017
From: Andre Santos-Silva <punkwolfe@gmail.com>


Mumps, human, Porto, Portugal
--------------------
At least four cases of mumps have been confirmed during the last week, and another is being investigated, in a small outbreak among university students aged 19-22, in Porto, Portugal. All patients had two doses of MMR vaccine.

Ongoing investigation seems to point to the index case being a toddler (age not specified) who is brother to one of the cases.
It is possible that more cases are still to appear, since the incubation period may go up to three weeks.

--
Communicated by:
Andre Santos-Silva
Centro Hospitalar de São João
Porto, Portugal
<punkwolfe@gmail.com>

[ProMED-mail would like to thank Dr. Santos-Silvia for sharing this information with us.

Mumps immunity, even following the complete series of 2 doses, may wane with time, and infection may occur especially with prolonged contact, as with a sibling in this case. However, having been fully vaccinated does partially protect preventing severe complications occasionally seen with unvaccinated individuals. 

